Functions
- computer values and cannot perform permanent environmental changes (no INSERT or UPDATE statements allowed)
- returns a value either a scalar or a table
- can have input parameters and can be used in inline SQL statements
- does not support transactions
- does not support exception handling
- can be joined upon if they return a result set (table)

Procedures
- handle larger activities and can modify data
- optionally return zero or multiple values
- can have input/output parameters
- can use transactions
- can call each other but cannot be used directly in SELECT, WHERE, OR HAVING statements

Functions - focused on computations
Procedures - handles complex tasks and allow data modification